WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.600 --> 00:00:13.530
Hong Kong is located on the southern coast
of The Peoples Republic of China.

00:00:13.530 --> 00:00:17.400
The former British colony consists of three
main areas;

00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:22.660
The New Territories, The Kowloon Peninsula,
and Hong Kong Island.

00:00:22.660 --> 00:00:26.869
Hong Kong is one of the most densely populated
places on the planet.

00:00:26.869 --> 00:00:30.230
It's dramatic cityscapes cling to the hillsides
and the edges

00:00:30.230 --> 00:00:32.689
of its spectacular harbor.

00:00:32.689 --> 00:00:38.730
Hong Kong is the embodiment of yin and yang,
the Chinese concept of balance.

00:00:38.730 --> 00:00:45.210
It is filled with neighborhoods that resonate
with Chinese and colonial tradition,

00:00:45.210 --> 00:00:49.030
while it's soaring skylines look boldly towards
the future.

00:00:49.030 --> 00:00:53.039
For visitors, Hong Kong offers some of the
world's most intense

00:00:53.039 --> 00:00:57.430
shopping, sightseeing and dining experiences,

00:00:57.430 --> 00:01:02.570
yet moments of stillness await at every turn.

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:07.619
Faith is an integral part of local life.

00:01:07.619 --> 00:01:12.970
Everywhere you go you'll smell the scent of
incense wafting from shrines.

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:16.399
Hong Kong has over 600 places of worship,

00:01:16.399 --> 00:01:20.160
from small neighborhood temples, to hilltop
complexes

00:01:20.160 --> 00:01:27.160
like the Ten Thousand Buddhas Monastery.

00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:32.849
In Hong Kong, shopping is almost a religion
too!

00:01:32.849 --> 00:01:34.630
From opulent malls like Pacific Place

00:01:34.630 --> 00:01:38.500
to the bustling markets of Temple Street and
Ladies Street,

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:43.530
tax-free Hong Kong is heaven bargain hunters.

00:01:43.530 --> 00:01:48.360
At the tip of the Kowloon Peninsula is Tsim
Sha Tsui,

00:01:48.360 --> 00:01:52.000
an area filled with classic neighborhoods.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:57.330
Take a stroll along the Tsim Sha Tsui Promenade
which overlooks Victoria Harbor,

00:01:57.330 --> 00:02:00.940
one of the busiest and most scenic ports in
the world.

00:02:00.940 --> 00:02:05.970
The promenade is home to some of the territories
premier arts institutions,

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:10.140
like the Museum of Art and the Hong Kong Cultural
Centre.

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:17.100
From the promenade, hop aboard an historic
Star Ferry

00:02:17.100 --> 00:02:20.100
for the short crossing to Hong Kong Island.

00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:27.970
Explore the malls and futuristic architecture
of Hong Kong's main business district, Central.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.900
Then take tram to the island's highest mountain,
Victoria Peak.

00:02:35.500 --> 00:02:41.280
At the Peak Tower, meet some of the giants
of history, politics, and popular culture

00:02:41.280 --> 00:02:42.410
at Madam Tussauds.

00:02:42.410 --> 00:02:49.410
Then head up to the observation deck for the
best views in Hong Kong.

00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:53.850
Looking down upon the skyscrapers and apartment
towers,

00:02:53.850 --> 00:02:59.180
you might wonder how so many people can live
in such a tightly packed area.

00:02:59.180 --> 00:03:03.760
Yet Hong Kong offers plenty of green spaces
too.

00:03:03.760 --> 00:03:08.210
Take a stroll around Lugard Road to experience
the Peak's dense woodlands.

00:03:08.210 --> 00:03:15.210
While closer to earth, Hong Kong's urban centers
feature pockets of peace everywhere.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.660
There's the wide open spaces of Victoria garden,

00:03:18.660 --> 00:03:22.480
the hillside tranquility of Hong Kong Garden,

00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:26.610
and the birdsong of the Po Lin Street Bird
Garden.

00:03:26.610 --> 00:03:33.370
Kowloon's Walled City Park is a gateway into
the world of classic Qing Dynasty design,

00:03:33.370 --> 00:03:39.590
and features statues of the twelve animals
of the Chinese zodiac.

00:03:39.590 --> 00:03:44.709
Outside the urban areas, visitors are often
surprised to learn

00:03:44.709 --> 00:03:50.200
that over forty percent of the Hong Kong's
territory has been designated as national park

00:03:50.600 --> 00:03:55.260
Thanks to Hong Kong's excellent public transport
system, quiet beaches,

00:03:55.260 --> 00:04:01.480
sparsely populated islands and wild places
are never more than short ride away.

00:04:01.480 --> 00:04:04.520
From Hong Kong Island's central business district,

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:09.240
take the half hour bus ride to the tranquil
beaches of Shek O.

00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:13.480
Or, jump on a ferry to traffic-free Lamma
Island

00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:19.579
and spend the day swimming, exploring villages,
and hiking its many trails.

00:04:19.579 --> 00:04:26.470
Lantau is the largest of Hong Kong's 250 Islands.

00:04:26.470 --> 00:04:31.120
Take the 25 minute cable car ride to the mountain-top
village of Ngong Ping.

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:37.250
Here you'll find the Po Lin Monastery, and
one of Hong Kong's biggest attractions, the

00:04:37.250 --> 00:04:41.630
Tian Tan Buddha.

00:04:41.630 --> 00:04:46.900
After paying your respects at the Big Buddha
seek a little enlightenment along the Wisdom Path

00:04:46.900 --> 00:04:53.130
a trail dedicated to the centuries-old Buddhist
scripture, the Heart Sutra.

00:04:54.300 --> 00:05:00.270
Down on Lantau's western coast, lose yourself
in the narrow lane ways of Tai O.

00:05:00.270 --> 00:05:02.590
This village has been home to fishing families
for generations.

00:05:02.590 --> 00:05:08.710
The ramshackle stilt houses are a favorite
with photographers,

00:05:08.710 --> 00:05:15.710
and its dried seafood is highly prized by
cooks from all over Hong Kong.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:22.000
In Hong Kong, no matter how far you roam,
you're never more than an hour from your hotel room.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:29.080
At the end of the day, let the outdoor escalators
on Central carry you up to the midlevel neighborhoods.

00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:34.770
Cruise the fashionable bars of Soho, then
choose a restaurant in the popular dinning

00:05:34.770 --> 00:05:37.830
district of Lan Kwai Fong.

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:44.830
Hong Kong is a place of contrasts after dark
too.

00:05:45.100 --> 00:05:50.880
Enjoy the bustle of the night markets, or
just sit back and relax by the cool of the harbor.

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:53.990
That's pure yin and yang.

00:05:53.990 --> 00:06:00.990
That's pure Hong Kong.

